# Catalog refresh — always use the latest skills & agents

The tool package (`.agents/pipeline.home` → `VERSION`) is the **source of truth** for
skills, agents, rules, and pack overlays. The repo copy under `.agents/` and host
projections (`.cursor/`) must match the installed `agentic-tool` version.

## When to refresh

Refresh **before SDLC work** when any of these is true:

- `agentic-tool` was updated/reinstalled on this machine
- `agentic-tool verify` warns **catalog stale**
- `pipeline.manifest.json` → `catalog_version` ≠ `agentic-tool version`
- A skill/agent/rule you need is missing or looks outdated

## Refresh workflow (mechanical)

```bash
# 1. Update the global tool (developers — from ai-dev-pipeline repo)
pwsh ./scripts/install-local.ps1
# or: dotnet tool update -g Agentic.Tool

# 2. Re-extract catalog into the repo (overwrites skills/agents/rules from package)
agentic-tool apply --target .

# 3. Re-project to host (.cursor/, CLAUDE.md, etc.)
agentic-tool sync --target . --host auto

# 4. Confirm
agentic-tool verify --target .
```

In agent chat (optional — re-detect stack if packs may have changed):

```text
Run .agents adapt --update
```

`apply` always copies **all** `alwaysSkills`, core agents, core rules, and active pack
overlays from the catalog. `sync` pushes them to the host. **Never hand-edit** files under
`.cursor/skills/` or `.cursor/rules/` — edit in `core/` or packs in the tool repo, then
re-apply.

## Coordinator / adapt rule

At session start, if `catalog_version` is behind `agentic-tool version`, **stop** and tell
the human to run `apply` + `sync` before continuing SDLC work.
